   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>(Cross) In the 7th year of the reign of our most divine and most august ruler, the greatest benefactor, Flavius Justinus, the eternal Augustus and emperor &lt;- - -&gt;, in the 6th indiction. Aurelius Phib, son of Phoibammon and Aeous, and Aurelius Ap, son of [. . .] and Sara, originating from the village of Great Mouchis of the Iustinopolite nome, with as guarantor . . ., son of . . ., from the same village, to Aurelius Papnouthios, from . . . of the same nome, greetings. I acknowledge that I have received from you, in full, the price [here] found satisfactory by me of one hundred and seven eight-sextarii jars of wine, total 107 eight-sextarii jars of wine which wine [- - -];;(Verso);;[. . .] Aurelius Phib, son of Phoibammon, and Aurelius Ap, [son of - - -]</ab>
         </div>
